DAMATURU – The General Hospital, Yusufari headquarters of Yusufari Local Government Council in Yobe would be commissioned in March this year to enhance healthcare service delivery at the grassroots. Head of Works of the Council who is the supervisor of the project, Bulama Umar, revealed this during an inspection visit by a team of journalists. He said that the project was initiated by Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni’s administration in December 2020, was designed to upgrade the existing health facility to general hospital status. Barber Stabs Motorcyclist To Death In Bayelsa Novena University College Of Law Commences LL.B Degree… According to him “We have done with the construction of the main building, which is about 75 per cent completion. “It has been roofed, plastered, piped and Plaster of Paris (POP) work is still ongoing, the remaining aspect is tilling and painting,” he said. He said the project is also designed with staff quarters, morgue, kitchen, laundry, mosque, toilets and walkways. Umar added that a 150KVA generator would be installed to ensure a steady power supply to the facility. While commending the contractor for quality work, the Head of Works also lauded the state government for ensuring the adequate release of funds to the project. POLL On his part, Chairman Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ) Yobe Council, Rajab Muhammed, the Team Lead, said that the inspection exercise was aimed at promoting transparency, accountability and good governance in the state. He urged them to sustain the tempo of commitment and seriousness of monitoring the project.